      "text": [
        " : \"أَنْزَلَ اَللَّهُ تَعَالَى عَلَى بَعْضِ أَنْبِيَائِهِ عَلَيْهِمُ اَلسَّلاَمُ لِلْكَرِيمِ فَكَارِمْ وَ لِلسَّمْحِ فَسَامِحْ وَ لِلشَّحِيحِ فَشَاحِحْ وَ عِنْدَ اَلشَّكِسِ فَالْتَوِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3734 - Isma'il ibn Muslim narrated from Abu Abdillah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), who said:\nAllah (swt), the Exalted, revealed to one of His prophets (peace be upon them): \"Deal generously with the generous, be lenient with the lenient, be tight-fisted with the stingy, and be evasive with the harsh.\""
        ]
      }
    },
